719329f-a.text:

719330f-a.text:
45 Dominicx Street, north side, east of Hudson Street. This is
the parsonage of the Spring Street Presbyterian Church, and is
the first of the houses in Greenwich Village remodelled by
Aailliam Sloane Coffin.
About 1915.

720515f-a.text:

inclusive. The very white building is the Evening Graphic Building,

October 11, 1928.
